Protestancy condemned by the expresse verdict and sentence of Protestants Knott, Edward, 1582-1656.
[10], 319, [1], 301-468, [22] p.
[s.n.], Doway printed : 1654.
Attributed to Knott by Wing and NUC pre-1956 imprints. Edward Knott was an English Jesuit whose real name was Matthew Wilson (and it is under the name of Wilson that he is identified by Wing); he assumed the name Edward Knott in 1602 and retained it throughout his life. Cf. DNB. Errata: p. [22] at end. Reproduction of original in the Union Theological Seminary Library, New York. Includes bibliographical references and index.
